The paper discusses the problem of software vulnerability to changes in run-time environments, operational conditions, and available resources, and proposes a solution called "New Software Development." This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential catastrophic consequences of software vulnerabilities, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a practical example of a software tool, which suggests that it may belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
